original_font_information.description: Amiri is a classical Arabic typeface in Naskh style for typesetting books and other running text. Its design is a revival of the beautiful typeface pioneered in early 20th century by Bulaq Press in Cairo, also known as Amiria Press, after which the font is named.

original_font_information.sampleText: صِفْ خَلْقَ خَوْدٍ كَمِثْلِ ٱلشَّمْسِ إِذْ بَزَغَتْ يَحْظَىٰ ٱلضَّجِيعُ بِهَا نَجْلَاءَ مِعْطَارِ.
original_font_information.unknown3: No automatic vowel insertion above name of God
original_font_information.unknown4: Low Baa dot following a Raa or Waw
original_font_information.unknown5: Alternate medial Meem and final Alef combination
original_font_information.unknown8: Kasra is placed below Shadda instead of base glyph
